  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6603 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-40.9B) and max positive gamma at 6610 (+87.5B), dealers are currently in accumulation mode, buying the dip as spot trades below the flip line at 6615. The massive +87.5B gamma wall at 6610 will trigger heavy dealer selling if breached, while the -40.9B negative gamma at 6590 creates an amplifying floor where dealer buying accelerates on any downside breach. The recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we're seeing dynamic repositioning, but the PIN regime favors mean reversion back toward the 6610-6615 zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pulled back up toward 6610-6615 with dealers providing buying support.",
